  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the career options after 12 in PCB?",
  "response": "After completing 12th grade with Physics, Chemistry, and Biology (PCB), there are numerous career options across various fields such as medicine, healthcare, research, and more. Here are some prominent career paths:\n\n### Medical and Healthcare Fields:\n1. **MBBS (Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery)**: To become a doctor.\n2. **BDS (Bachelor of Dental Surgery)**: To become a dentist.\n3. **BAMS (Bachelor of Ayurvedic Medicine and Surgery)**: For a career in Ayurveda.\n4. **BHMS (Bachelor of Homeopathic Medicine and Surgery)**: For a career in Homeopathy.\n5. **BUMS (Bachelor of Unani Medicine and Surgery)**: For a career in Unani medicine.\n6. **BPT (Bachelor of Physiotherapy)**: For a career in physiotherapy.\n7. **B.V.Sc. & AH (Bachelor of Veterinary Science and Animal Husbandry)**: To become a veterinarian.\n8. **B.Sc. Nursing**: For a career in nursing.\n9. **B.Pharm (Bachelor of Pharmacy)**: To become a pharmacist.\n10. **B.Sc. Medical Imaging Technology**: For careers in radiology and imaging.\n11. **B.Sc. in Optometry**: For a career as an optometrist.\n\n### Paramedical and Allied Health Sciences:\n12. **B.Sc. in Medical Laboratory Technology (MLT)**: For a career in diagnostic laboratories.\n13. **B.Sc. in Operation Theatre Technology (OTT)**: For operation theatre management.\n14. **B.Sc. in Dialysis Technology**: For careers in nephrology.\n15. **B.Sc. in Cardiac Care Technology**: For careers in cardiology.\n16. **B.Sc. in Nutrition and Dietetics**: For careers in nutrition and diet planning.\n\n### Research and Academics:\n17. **B.Sc. in Biotechnology**: For careers in biotech research and development.\n18. **B.Sc. in Microbiology**: For microbiology and related research.\n19. **B.Sc. in Biochemistry**: For biochemical research and analysis.\n20. **B.Sc. in Environmental Science**: For careers in environmental research and conservation.\n\n### Alternative Medicine:\n21. **Bachelor of Naturopathy & Yogic Science (BNYS)**: For careers in naturopathy.\n22. **B.Sc. in Yoga and Physical Education**: For careers in yoga instruction and wellness.\n\n### Other Career Options:\n23. **Pharmaceutical Sciences**: For drug development and manufacturing.\n24. **Biomedical Engineering**: For developing medical devices and equipment.\n25. **Forensic Science**: For careers in forensic investigation.\n26. **Wildlife Biology**: For careers in wildlife conservation and research.\n27. **Food Technology**: For careers in food science and technology.\n28. **Agricultural Science**: For careers in agriculture and related fields.\n29. **B.Sc. in Genetic Engineering**: For careers in genetic research and engineering.\n\n### Integrated and Dual Degree Programs:\n30. **Integrated M.Sc. Programs**: Direct entry into master's programs in various science disciplines.\n31. **Dual Degree Programs**: Combining undergraduate and postgraduate studies in specialized fields.\n\n### Competitive Exams and Further Studies:\n32. **NEET (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test)**: For admission to medical and dental colleges.\n33. **AIIMS (All India Institute of Medical Sciences) Entrance Exam**: For admission to AIIMS.\n34. **JIPMER (Jawaharlal Institute of Postgraduate Medical Education and Research) Entrance Exam**: For admission to JIPMER.\n35. **Other State-level Medical Entrance Exams**: For state medical colleges.\n\n### Professional Certifications:\n36. **Certification in Clinical Research**: For careers in clinical research organizations.\n37. **Certification in Medical Coding**: For careers in healthcare administration and billing.\n\n### Entrepreneurship:\n38. **Healthcare Startups**: Starting your own healthcare-related business.\n39. **Medical Tourism**: Developing businesses in medical tourism.\n\n### Specialized Fields:\n40. **B.Sc. in Marine Biology**: For careers in marine research and conservation.\n41. **B.Sc. in Zoology**: For careers in animal biology and research.\n42. **B.Sc. in Botany**: For careers in plant biology and research.\n\nThese options provide a wide range of opportunities depending on your interests, aptitude, and career goals. Further research and counseling can help you choose the most suitable path.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
